design_brief_for_codex.firestore_security_rules:
Add `muno/firestore.rules` documenting the v1 permissive ruleset. Don't deploy it from this round — Kadyapam can apply it via `firebase deploy --only firestore:rules` from his local environment OR via gcloud after the round merges. Sample:
```
rules_version = '2';
service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {
    match /chat_threads/{thread}/{document=**} {
      allow read: if true;  // v1 permissive; tighten when Firebase Auth lands
      allow write: if false; // writes happen via worker SA only
    }
    match /trips/{trip}/{document=**} {
      allow read: if true;
      allow write: if false;
    }
    match /users/{uid}/{document=**} {
      allow read: if true;  // v1 demo; per-user rules in post-tutorial round
      allow write: if false;
    }
  }
}
```
Document in `muno/docs/deployment/firestore-rules.md` that these rules are demo-permissive and the deployment step is manual.
